KAIZER Chiefs will appeal the ban imposed by Fifa over the transfer of Madagascan midfielder Andriamirado ‘Dax’ Andrianarimanana, the club have confirmed. READ: FIFA BANS CHIEFS, DAX Chiefs signed the 28-year-old at the begininng of 2018/19 season, but a dispute between Dax and his former club Fosa Juniors over his contract, stalled his debut. Dax was eventualy cleared by Fifa to play for Chiefs. However, his former team refused to give up and won their appeal, leading to the transfer ban for two windows imposed by Fifa on both the player and Chiefs. But Chiefs are not prepared to take the ban lying down and have decided to lodge their own appeal before the Court of Arbitration for Sport "The Club and the player have received a correspondence from FIFA Disciplinary Committee concerning the Malagasy player Adriamirado Aro Hasina Andrianarimanana."Kaizer Chiefs will lodge an appeal before the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) in accordance to article 58 par. 1 of the FIFA Statutes," read a statemnet from the club. 